\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 127. S. asterias }Griseb., {\i Spicil. Fl. Rumel.}{\b  1}: 168 (1843). Like {\b 125} but a rhizomatous perennial; stems up to 100 cm; inflorescence capitate, subtended by membranous bracts; cauline leaves few, lanceolate; calyx-teeth acute; petal-limb oblong, entire, deep purple; coronal scales short; capsule 5-7 mm, slightly shorter than the carpophore.{\i  Marshy places. • From N.W. Greece to N.W. Bulgaria.} Al Bu Gr Ju.
